Hi,
I am trying to add a code similar to "ComputeThermalExpansionEigenstrain" with something like "ComputeThermalExpansionEigenstrainOrthotropic" where I want to provide 3 values of thermal expansion coefficient. To do that I did the following:
Added a method in RankTwoTensorImplementation.h similar to addIa(a) :
void
RankTwoTensorTempl<T>::addDiag(const T & a)
{
  for (auto i : make_range(N))
    (*this)(i, i) += a(i);
}
The objective is to have the diagonal components added to the vector (which would be a non-isotropic eigenstrain)
Subsequently, I followed "ComputeThermalExpansionEigenstrain" to write a new code "ComputeThermalExpansionEigenstrainOrthotropic" where I am taking 3 thermal expansion coefficients and the new "computeThermalStrain()" looks something like:
template <bool is_ad>
ValueAndDerivative<is_ad>
ComputeThermalExpansionEigenstrainOrthotropicTempl<is_ad>::computeThermalStrain()
{
  _diagonal_strain_components(1) = _thermal_expansion_coeff_11 * (_temperature[_qp] - _stress_free_temperature[_qp]);
  _diagonal_strain_components(2) = _thermal_expansion_coeff_22 * (_temperature[_qp] - _stress_free_temperature[_qp]);
  _diagonal_strain_components(3) = _thermal_expansion_coeff_33 * (_temperature[_qp] - _stress_free_temperature[_qp]);
  return _diagonal_strain_components ;
}
with the _diagonal_strain_components being a std of size 3 that has the eigenstrain components.
Now my question is-- to add this to the _eigenstrain[_qp] in the computeQpEigenstrain in "ComputeThermalExpansionEigenstrainBase", how do I modify such that when the thermal_strain is a vector it uses the aforementioned .addDiag(thermal_strain.value()) instead of .addIa(thermal_strain.value()) :
template <bool is_ad>
void
ComputeThermalExpansionEigenstrainBaseTempl<is_ad>::computeQpEigenstrain()
{
  _eigenstrain[_qp].zero();
  const auto thermal_strain = computeThermalStrain();

  if constexpr (is_ad)
    _eigenstrain[_qp].addIa(thermal_strain);
  else
  {
    _eigenstrain[_qp].addIa(thermal_strain.value());
    (*_deigenstrain_dT)[_qp].zero();
    if (!_use_old_temperature)
      (*_deigenstrain_dT)[_qp].addIa(thermal_strain.derivatives());
  }
}
One thing I was thinking was to put a flag to check whether the thermal_strain is a scalar or a vector and use accordingly, but I am not sure if that makes sense...
Also, for my case where thermal_strain is a vector can I still use thermal_strain.derivatives() and thermal_strain.values() ?
(P.S. New Moose user and trying my hand at small modifications :( )
Any suggestions/comments would be extremely helpful.
Thanks,
Aritra

